n bunkers started to peak and 70mt were stemmed at $1,286/mt. We also had a few additional expenses to prep for Proman; FW purchase was required and we asked GAM\u2019s agents to assist in embarking our Lighthouse supercargo at NOLA. Lighthouse was engaged due very poor onboard handling of Palms discharge by sister vessel Dianella (more to follow), at this point we had zero trust that the vessel would be able to present tanks ready for Proman so the earlier we could embark Mr. Jay to assist the better."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-05-05T14:08:24.413","modifiedByFull":"Andersen, Thomas","remark":"BOR bought from GAM in calc. as an expenses, positive effect \u002B 325 tUSD"}],"offhireList":[{"id":189657,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":32214,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":{"fixtureRemarks":null,"deliveryDateTimeZ":"2021-12-27T16:01:00","deliveryLegName":"Davao"}}